{"article_id":"fB3KnfeMzfFmXvcB","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Trump has gone back to the drawing board on tax reform","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"as he looks for wide-ranging Republican support behind legislation","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to overhaul the tax system .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"A White House official told Fox Business Network","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that all options are still on the table .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"However , a detailed tax plan is still weeks away .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"A complete tax overhaul will likely miss the August deadline","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"set by Treasury Secretary Mnuchin .","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"The White House is trying to learn from the failure","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"of enacting a new health care law","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"to replace ObamaCare","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"and take a more active role","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"in getting legislation passed .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"White House aides told The Associated Press Monday","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"that the goal is to cut tax rates sharply enough","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"to improve the economic picture in rural and industrial areas of the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"However , the administration so far has swatted down alternative ways","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"for raising revenues ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"such as a carbon tax ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"to offset lower rates .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Trump has not said","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"which trade-offs he might accept","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and had remained noncommittal on the leading blueprint for reform from Rep. Kevin Brady , R-Texas , the chairman of the Ways and Means Committee .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Brady has proposed a border adjustment system ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"which would eliminate corporate deductions on imports ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to raise $ 1 trillion over 10 years","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"that could fund lower corporate tax rates .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"But that possibility has rankled retailers","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"who say","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"it would lead to higher prices","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"and threaten millions of jobs ,","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"while some lawmakers have worried","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"that the system would violate World Trade Organization rules .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Brady has said","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"he intends to amend the blueprint","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"but has not spelled out how he would do so .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Another option","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"being floated around on Capitol Hill","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"would change the House GOP plan","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"to eliminate much of the payroll tax","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"and cut corporate tax rates","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"and possibly requiring a new dedicated funding source for Social Security .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"The change ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"proposed by a GOP lobbyist with close ties to the Trump administration ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"would transform Brady 's plan on imports into something closer to a value-added tax","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"by also eliminating the deduction of labor expenses .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"This would bring it in line with WTO rules","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and generate an additional $ 12 trillion over 10 years ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"according to budget estimates .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"Those additional revenues could then enable the end of the 12.4 percent payroll tax ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"split evenly between employers and employees ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"that funds Social Security ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"while keeping the health insurance payroll tax in place .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"This approach would give a worker","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"earning $ 60,000 a year","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"an additional $ 3,720 in take-home pay , a possible win","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that lawmakers could highlight back in their districts","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"even though it would involve changing the funding mechanism for Social Security ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"according to the lobbyist .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Sen . Rob Portman , R-Ohio , a member of the Senate Finance Committee , said","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"that all of the trial balloons","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"surfacing in public","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"do n't represent the work","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"that 's being done behind the scenes .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"`` It 's not really what 's going on , ''","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Portman said .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"`` What 's going on is they 're working with on various ideas . ''","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"The White House has not officially commented on any plan ,","depth":2},{"id":68,"text":"but said in a statement","depth":3},{"id":69,"text":"but said","depth":4},{"id":70,"text":"a value-added tax","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"based on consumption","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"is not under consideration `` as of now . \"","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":145,"left":139,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":80,"right":138,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":80,"left":78,"right":79,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":78,"left":75,"right":77,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":0,"right":74,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":74,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":76,"right":5,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":79,"left":6,"right":7,"relation